This paper is primarily focused on image and video classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for feature learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of custom designed network structures for pixels and optical flow, which are both related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
